The evidence with the title 'Disconnected duct syndrome: a Bridge To Nowhere ' says Disconnected duct syndrome (dds) is defined by a complete discontinuity of the pancreatic duct , such that a viable left side of the pancreas does not drain downstream into the duodenum , through an intact duct that traverses the length of the pancreas [ 1 -4].This syndrome occurs predominately in the pancreatic neck region ,  ... 
